separated from each other, so then
according to the minhag Lita, and

220
00:21:09,801 --> 00:21:14,072
in accordance with many opinions
of poskim, gedolei Acharonim,

221
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:17,209
you read Ki'vnei Kushiyim twice;

222
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:25,751
on Shabbos of Acharei Mos, as well
as on the Shabbos of Kedoshim.

223
00:21:26,518 --> 00:21:31,223
"Ha'lo ki'vnei Kushiyim atem
li Bnei Yisrael ne'um Adoshem

224
00:21:31,223 --> 00:21:41,667
ha'lo es Yisrael he'eleisi mei'eretz
Mitzrayim u'Phlishtiyim mi'Kaftor

225
00:21:41,667 --> 00:21:45,804
va'Aram mi'Kir."  We don't understand the relationship

226
00:21:46,438 --> 00:21:48,974
of that portion of that prophecy

227
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:53,645
 to Acharei Mos, to the laws

228
00:21:54,713 --> 00:21:59,217
and halachos formulated 

229
00:21:59,217 --> 00:22:03,021
in the parshah of Acharei Mos or Kedoshim.

230
00:22:03,021 --> 00:22:06,024
There is no similarity

231
00:22:06,024 --> 00:22:10,062
at all between the
Haftarah and the parshiyos.

232
00:22:10,062 --> 00:22:11,630
What is the reason, actually?

233
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:16,034
What is the reason that we replaced
the Haftaros from Yechezkel

234
00:22:16,034 --> 00:22:19,504
with a Haftarah of Amos?

235
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,044
Of course, there is no mystery.

236
00:22:26,044 --> 00:22:28,714
I mean, the answer is very simple.

237
00:22:28,714 --> 00:22:30,716
At least the first answer is simple.

238
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:36,888
Then, another question arises, and we'll
have difficulty in solving this question.

239
00:22:37,756 --> 00:22:38,990
There is no mystery at all.

240
00:22:39,958 --> 00:22:44,329
There is a Baraisa in Megillah,
at the end of Megillah,

241
00:22:46,631 --> 00:22:49,267
as well as in Mesechet Sofrim,

242
00:22:51,670 --> 00:22:55,407
which quotes the opinion of Rabbi Eliezer.

243
00:22:57,075 --> 00:22:59,578
Rabbi Eliezer says,

244
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:08,153
"Ein maftirin b'to'avos Yerushalayim,"
you should not recite the prophecies about

245
00:23:08,153 --> 00:23:16,061
to'avos, the abominations of Yerushalayim,
"kol ikar," you don't mention them at all.

246
00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:18,730
Neither for Acharei Mos, nor for Kedoshim.

247
00:23:19,264 --> 00:23:20,832
We shouldn't.

248
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:29,741
"Ma'aseh b'echad" -- in Mesechet Sofrim,
as well as in the Gemara in Megillah, it

249
00:23:29,741 --> 00:23:36,148
says, "Ma'aseh b'echad," it happened that
some individual, "haya korei lema'alah

250
00:23:36,148 --> 00:23:37,549
m'Rabbi Eliezer," he was probably on

251
00:23:37,549 --> 00:23:39,050
the second floor, Rabbi Eliezer
was on the street floor.

252
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:44,423
"Lema'alah m'Rabbi Eliezer," I
mean, geographically, as far as in

253
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:49,094
spatial terms, he was above Rabbi
Eliezer, "b'to'avos Yerushalayim,"

254
00:23:49,661 --> 00:23:53,832
he recited the Maftir for Acharei
Mos or Kedoshim, 

255
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:59,037
the Haftarah from To'avos 
Yerushalayim from Yechezkel.

256
00:24:00,205 --> 00:24:05,010
"Amar lo Rabbi Eliezer," so Rabbi
Eliezer told him, "reika," fool, "ad

257
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:11,950
sh'atah bodek b'to'avos Yerushalayim,"
you are so interested to indict

258
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:14,820
Yerushalayim of all crimes, "tzei u'vdok

259
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:19,691
b'imach," investigate your maternal
background, the family tree.

260
00:24:19,691 --> 00:24:25,497
So, the Mesechet Sofrim says,
"U'matzo b'imo sh'hee pesulah," and

261
00:24:25,497 --> 00:24:31,169
they found some p'sul as far
as the mother was concerned.

262
00:24:31,803 --> 00:24:38,844
True, the Gemara in Megillah says,
"L'afukei mi'd'Rabbi Eliezer," the

263
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:40,512
halachah is not like Rabbi Eliezer.

264
00:24:41,079 --> 00:24:44,983
That's what the Gemara in Megillah
says, but Mesechet Sofrim didn't say it.

265
00:24:44,983 --> 00:24:49,588
Mesechet Sofrim quoted Rabbi
Eliezer, and apparently,

266
00:24:49,588 --> 00:24:53,091
because he's in full
agreement with Rabbi Eliezer.

267
00:24:53,959 --> 00:24:58,797
This means that according to Mesechet
Sofrim, is the halachah like

268
00:24:58,797 --> 00:24:59,965
Rabbi Eliezer?

269
00:24:59,965 --> 00:25:02,801
So, since the halachah is
like Rabbi Eliezer, so the two

270
00:25:02,801 --> 00:25:08,373
Haftaros from Yechezkel, Chaf or
Chaf-Beis, are ruled out and they

271
00:25:08,373 --> 00:25:15,847
are replaced by another Haftarah,
namely, K'vnei Kushiyim from Amos.

272
00:25:22,888 --> 00:25:26,892
And as I said before, and we are

273
00:25:26,892 --> 00:25:33,765
so careful and meticulous about
it that in a leap year, we read

274
00:25:33,765 --> 00:25:37,802
the Haftarah of Amos twice.

275
00:25:38,670 --> 00:25:44,609
Only a few Haftaros are read and
reread during the year, during the

276
00:25:44,609 --> 00:25:47,312
annual cycle, but here it stopped.

277
00:25:47,312 --> 00:25:48,713
A plain Haftarah is

278
00:25:48,713 --> 00:25:56,454
recited for Acharei Mos and the
same is recited for Kedoshim.

279
00:26:02,694 --> 00:26:08,199
Of course, we have accepted Rabbi
Eliezer's opinion that a Jew who

280
00:26:08,199 --> 00:26:12,070
bought Maftir for $25 has no right to

281
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:15,307
criticize Jerusalem.

282
00:26:22,113 --> 00:26:26,585
He has no right to repeat the
words of the Navi, of the Prophet.

283
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:34,893
And he should not charge Yerushalayim
with the Maftir, with crime, great sins

284
00:26:34,893 --> 00:26:36,928
and transgressions and abominations.

285
00:26:36,928 --> 00:26:38,697
He has no right.

286
00:26:40,732 --> 00:26:48,273
The question here -- now, I mean, if
you could state the question, so that's

287
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:53,712
why we have replaced the Haftaros
of Achrei Mos-Kedoshim as far as the

288
00:26:53,712 --> 00:26:55,013
nevuah of Yechezkel is concerned.

289
00:26:55,013 --> 00:26:56,381
We don't recite it.

290
00:26:56,381 --> 00:26:57,048
Fine.

291
00:26:57,048 --> 00:27:00,619
Yeah, but there is still a question,
I mean, I haven't answered.

292
00:27:03,088 --> 00:27:04,356
Why Amos?

293
00:27:04,356 --> 00:27:04,856
Correct.

294
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:06,758
Why Amos?

295
00:27:07,058 --> 00:27:15,900
Chazal, Chachmei Yisrael could've chosen
or selected another Haftarah which

296
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:21,139
has some similarity to the parshiyos

297
00:27:21,139 --> 00:27:27,045
ha'Torah, which had
something in common with the

298
00:27:27,045 --> 00:27:28,913
parshiyos ha'Torah, with the kri'a.

299
00:27:29,180 --> 00:27:33,485
We have chosen the
Haftarah of the first Navi,

300
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:41,660
Amos, which, prima facie, at first glance,
there's absolutely no relationship to

301
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:47,832
whatever the Torah has formulated in
Acharei Mos and Kedoshim, not at all.

302
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:58,109
At first glance, not a single sentence
unites Amos with the parshiyos

303
00:27:58,109 --> 00:28:00,645
Kedoshim and Acharei Mos in the Torah.

304
00:28:03,715 --> 00:28:05,717
The answer, I believe, is obvious.

305
00:28:05,717 --> 00:28:07,152
It's not difficult.

306
00:28:12,490 --> 00:28:17,629
Both sidros -- that means
Acharei Mos and Kedoshim

307
00:28:22,133 --> 00:28:23,702
-- told the people something

308
00:28:26,504 --> 00:28:27,672
which frightened them.

309
00:28:29,874 --> 00:28:32,944
They addressed to the 
people for the first time

310
00:28:33,478 --> 00:28:42,787
since they left Mitzrayim, for the first
time, something frightening, horrifying.

311
00:28:45,090 --> 00:28:46,791
Namely, what?

312
00:28:48,860 --> 00:28:54,599
That there is a possibility, and perhaps not
only a possibility but a probability

313
00:28:54,599 --> 00:29:01,873
or perhaps a certainty, that in
the future, they'll lose the land

314
00:29:05,944 --> 00:29:11,750
and they will be exiled from
their ancestral land 

315
00:29:13,518 --> 00:29:18,356
into an endless, bleak 
and dreary galut.

316
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:25,597
There is a reality,

317
00:29:25,597 --> 00:29:29,501
which we call galut, that was
disclosed to the people in Acharei

318
00:29:29,501 --> 00:29:31,870
Mos and Kedoshim for the first time.

319
00:29:34,339 --> 00:29:40,078
The Torah says for the first time
-- later, the Torah repeated this warning

320
00:29:40,078 --> 00:29:45,483
of what the Acharei Mos-Kedoshim -- the
people to whom Acharei Mos-Kedoshim

321
00:29:45,483 --> 00:29:51,055
was revealed through Moshe, by Hakadosh
Baruch Hu through Moshe, were taken aback.

322
00:29:51,656 --> 00:29:53,324
What did they hear?

323
00:29:53,324 --> 00:29:59,063
They heard a few sentences, which
they did not understand a word and

324
00:29:59,063 --> 00:30:01,833
they got frightened, horrified.

325
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,334
What happened?

326
00:30:03,668 --> 00:30:08,807
"Ki es kol ha'to'eivos ha'eil,"
all those abominations, "asu

327
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:11,242
anshei ha'aretz asher lifneichem,"

328
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:19,150
were committed by the people of
the land who preceded your coming

329
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:26,858
to the land, "va'titma ha'aretz,"
and the land became defiled.

330
00:30:29,961 --> 00:30:31,563
"V'lo saki ha'aretz

331
00:30:31,563 --> 00:30:35,266
es'chem," and the land
should not vomit you out,

332
00:30:35,266 --> 00:30:37,068
cast you out.

333
00:30:43,141 --> 00:30:50,415
This is in Acharei Mos,
Vayikra Chaf-Teis, Chaf-Cheis.

334
00:30:50,415 --> 00:30:52,617
Then in Kedoshim,

335
00:30:52,617 --> 00:30:58,389
"U'shmartem es kol chukosai v'es kol
mishpatai va'asisem osam v'lo saki

336
00:30:58,389 --> 00:31:02,594
ha'aretz," the same expression, the same
idiom, "v'lo saki ha'aretz es'chem," the

337
00:31:02,594 --> 00:31:06,030
land will not throw you up, vomit you out.

338
00:31:06,531 --> 00:31:08,199
It's a very strange word.

339
00:31:09,567 --> 00:31:15,240
"Asher ani meivi es'chem shamah la'sheves
bah," to which I brought you in order to

340
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:18,076
live there for many, many, many years.

341
00:31:18,443 --> 00:31:25,383
But should you commit those abominations,
so the land will simply shake you off.

342
00:31:26,818 --> 00:31:30,655
As a matter of fact,

343
00:31:32,857 --> 00:31:39,731
the Torah emphasizes that exile
from the land, or departure from the

344
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:45,203
land, in such a case, is a natural

345
00:31:47,472 --> 00:31:50,375
phenomenon, not a penalty.

346
00:31:51,276 --> 00:31:54,312
It is a phenomenon which
can be explained in

347
00:31:54,312 --> 00:31:57,548
terms of cause and effect.

348
00:31:57,548 --> 00:32:01,052
In causal terms, it could be understood.

349
00:32:01,052 --> 00:32:07,659
It's not a special onesh imposed
upon the Jewish people, but it is

350
00:32:08,026 --> 00:32:14,232
an -- it is a result of certain
behavior on the part of the people.

351
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:24,575
It is almost -- I mean, it fits
into the scheme of causality,

352
00:32:24,575 --> 00:32:26,277
of cause and effect.

353
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:35,920
The land in words -- the land
does not tolerate immorality,

354
00:32:36,454 --> 00:32:44,262
particularly immorality of
arayos and murder and bloodshed.

355
00:32:44,262 --> 00:32:51,936
And it casts off the people who defile
themselves with such abominable deeds.

356
00:32:53,237 --> 00:33:01,212
The way Rashi says, a prince with
a very delicate digestive system

357
00:33:01,846 --> 00:33:10,288
will throw up if he'll be fed
food which is slightly spoiled.

358
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:15,393
Eretz Yisrael is a very delicate,

359
00:33:17,362 --> 00:33:19,597
a very tender land.

360
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:23,334
It does not tolerate every aveirah.

361
00:33:24,068 --> 00:33:25,436
It does not tolerate it.

362
00:33:25,436 --> 00:33:26,704
It shakes them off.

363
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,042
You don't have to be punished for that.

364
00:33:31,042 --> 00:33:33,511
It's simply the soil.

365
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:37,749
The particles of the soil
shake off every aveirah.

366
00:33:39,384 --> 00:33:44,722
Rashi says, "Mashal l'ben
melech sh'he'echiluhu

367
00:33:44,722 --> 00:33:48,760
davar ma'us sh'ein omed

368
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:59,370
b'mei'av u'meki'o kach Eretz
Yisrael einah mekayemes aleiha ovrei

369
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:02,540
aveirah." This is what Rashi says.

370
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:09,981
Like the prince who throws up if he
was fed something which was spoiled or

371
00:34:09,981 --> 00:34:16,020
not the best or finest quality, because
he has a delicate digestive system,

372
00:34:17,255 --> 00:34:19,991
so is Eretz Yisrael very sensitive.

373
00:34:20,625 --> 00:34:25,663
Certain aveiros in chutz
la'aretz are differently assessed

374
00:34:27,298 --> 00:34:29,333
than they would have
been in Eretz Yisrael.

375
00:34:30,968 --> 00:34:36,174
Eretz Yisrael not as a ben melech but
a bas melech, very, very delicate,

376
00:34:36,174 --> 00:34:39,143
very tender, very meticulous.

377
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:43,214
And galus is not a punishment.

378
00:34:43,214 --> 00:34:46,150
It is the natural consequence of cheit.

379
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:50,021
That's what Rashi wanted to explain.

380
00:35:00,398 --> 00:35:01,499
Nu?

381
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:03,534
So what?

382
00:35:05,503 --> 00:35:09,040
And this the people
heard for the first time.

383
00:35:10,341 --> 00:35:15,546
They heard that Eretz Yisrael
casts off, casts out sinners

384
00:35:17,014 --> 00:35:20,751
or those who defile themselves
and defile the land

385
00:35:20,751 --> 00:35:22,086
with their deeds.

386
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:35,433
So, wouldn't you say that the Chachamim
who actually dealt with this problem

387
00:35:35,433 --> 00:35:39,804
of a Haftarah to choose the proper
Haftarah for Acharei Mos and Kedoshim

388
00:35:40,771 --> 00:35:44,809
faced -- what shall I say -- a dilemma?

389
00:35:47,745 --> 00:35:49,614
There were two possibilities.

390
00:35:50,214 --> 00:35:59,790
One possibility is that the topic,
the theme of Kedoshim and Acharei Mos

391
00:36:00,691 --> 00:36:10,434
should be, I mean, the laws pertaining
to arayos, to avodah zarah, to murder.

392
00:36:11,135 --> 00:36:21,812
In Kedoshim, the laws pertaining
to Shabbos, to Kibud Av va'Em.

393
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:23,714
They could have

394
00:36:23,714 --> 00:36:31,756
found such a prophecy or a portion
which would correspond, which would run

395
00:36:31,756 --> 00:36:38,095
parallel to those basic laws which are
mentioned in Kedoshim or Acharei Mos.

396
00:36:38,095 --> 00:36:43,401
Rashi, at the beginning of
Kedoshim, says this parshah includes

397
00:36:43,401 --> 00:36:46,070
"gufei Torah," the very tenets 

398
00:36:48,005 --> 00:36:50,174
of our Torah.

399
00:36:50,174 --> 00:36:56,514
So, it was quite possible, I mean,
to choose some chapter in Isaiah or

400
00:36:56,514 --> 00:37:01,819
in Yechezkel or any other book of
Prophets which would correspond, 

401
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:06,657
would run parallel to 
the gufei Torah which

402
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:12,930
were formulated in Kedoshim
as well as in Emor.

403
00:37:14,966 --> 00:37:19,237
There's another -- this is one
alternative, one possibility, but the

404
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:25,376
Chachamim had another possibility,
namely, to declare the central theme

405
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:27,278
of Acharei Mos and Kedoshim 

406
00:37:27,745 --> 00:37:28,746
is

407
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:31,582
galus.

408
00:37:33,851 --> 00:37:39,156
The central theme consists in this
sentence: "V'lo saki ha'aretz es'chem."

409
00:37:39,991 --> 00:37:42,526
We have the Maftir has got to react

410
00:37:44,095 --> 00:37:49,700
to that theme, to the theme of
galus, which was new, something

411
00:37:49,700 --> 00:37:53,504
new and incomprehensible to them.

412
00:37:55,206 --> 00:38:03,347
The Chachamim had the choice either
to prefer the gufei Torah and declare

413
00:38:03,347 --> 00:38:07,852
them as the central theme of Kedoshim,
and then fashion the Haftarah in

414
00:38:07,852 --> 00:38:10,588
accordance with the gufei Torah.

415
00:38:11,188 --> 00:38:13,758
"V'lo sechakashu v'lo
seshakeru. V'lo sishavu bi'shmi

416
00:38:13,758 --> 00:38:16,160
la'shaker." Important mitzvos.

417
00:38:16,727 --> 00:38:19,263
"Ish imo v'aviv tira'u
v'es Shabbsosai tishmoru.

418
00:38:19,697 --> 00:38:23,000
Lo salin pe'ulas sachir it'cha ad boker.

419
00:38:23,301 --> 00:38:25,403
V'ahavta l'rei'acha kamocha.

420
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:32,843
V'yareisa Adoshem Elokecha." Those
laws, tenets, principles of morality,

421
00:38:32,843 --> 00:38:37,048
the basic principles of morality,
could have become the central theme

422
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:41,419
of Kedoshim, and the Haftarah would
have been fashioned in accordance with

423
00:38:41,419 --> 00:38:47,091
those principles, would correspond to
those -- with those principles. However,

424
00:38:47,091 --> 00:38:49,260
the Chachamim decided differently.

425
00:38:50,594 --> 00:38:52,396
If the Haftarah "Ha'lo ki'vnei

426
00:38:52,396 --> 00:38:57,735
Kushiyim atem Beis Yisrael " is

427
00:38:57,735 --> 00:38:59,570
accepted, so what is

428
00:38:59,570 --> 00:39:00,905
the central theme?

429
00:39:01,539 --> 00:39:06,243
What is the central theme
of Acharei Mos and Kedoshim?

430
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:07,511
What?

431
00:39:10,047 --> 00:39:11,048
Galus.

432
00:39:11,582 --> 00:39:15,119
And how to avoid it, the Haftarah should

433
00:39:15,119 --> 00:39:15,820
answer how

434
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,254
to avoid galus,

435
00:39:18,255 --> 00:39:20,791
how not to be trapped by galus.

436
00:39:20,791 --> 00:39:25,663
Not to be confronted
by that curse of galus.

437
00:39:26,130 --> 00:39:28,599
And if, Rachmana litzlan, chas v'shalom,

438
00:39:29,533 --> 00:39:36,340
a Jew should be exiled from his
land, how to get back to the land.

439
00:39:40,411 --> 00:39:47,418
And that is why Chazal chose
